Implemented `noscope-s9i` as a TDD cleanup focused on module hygiene and test placement.

- I started with red by adding `module_hygiene_tests` in `src/lib.rs` that enforce both bead rules, then ran `cargo test module_hygiene_tests` and confirmed both tests failed first.
- I fixed rule 1 by changing crate root export from `pub mod ci_checks;` to `#[cfg(test)] mod ci_checks;` in `src/lib.rs`.
- I fixed rule 2 by moving the SignalHandlingPolicy unit tests into `src/signal_policy.rs` under `#[cfg(test)] mod tests`, and deleting `tests/signal_handling_policy.rs`.
- I added the offline provenance draft at `.beads/provenance-drafts/noscope-s9i.md` per your required format.

Linus-style self-review (brutal pass) found one legitimate issue: the initial hygiene assertion was too loose and could be semantically ambiguous; I tightened coverage by adding `ci_checks_is_gated_to_test_builds` in `src/lib.rs` to explicitly check for `#[cfg(test)]\nmod ci_checks;`.

